In a series of interviews, various members of the Trump administration discussed their views on the proposed healthcare bill and other issues. Secretary of Health and Human Services Tom Price emphasized the need for a healthcare system that works for people, giving them choices and reducing costs. Director of the Office of Management and Budget Mick Mulvaney stated that the bill aims to repeal and replace Obamacare, and encouraged Congress to make improvements to the bill. Director of the National Economic Council Gary Cohn expressed the President's willingness to accept improvements to the bill and his desire for more options for consumers. Counselor to the President Kellyanne Conway highlighted the President's commitment to action and the importance of protecting the nation's sovereignty and borders. Commerce Secretary Wilbur Ross discussed the need for fair trade agreements to protect American jobs. Director Mulvaney further emphasized the failure of Obamacare and the need to ensure affordable access to healthcare.